The paper discusses model compression with a focus on maintaining robustness to adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) research. The proposed framework involves optimization and constraint formulation, which are also common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography (cs.CR) research. Additionally, the paper presents experimental results, which could fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS) if the experiments involve testing the efficiency of the proposed algorithm.
